Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled into roughly 1cm pieces) into roughly 1cm
pieces. Peel the @carrot{1}(peeled and top and bottom removed) and chop into
roughly 1cm pieces. Peel and grate all but one of the @garlic cloves{2} (or use
a #garlic press{}). Slice the @aubergine{1}(sliced into discs approximately 1cm
thick) into discs approximately 1cm thick.

Heat a splash of @oil{a splash} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat and add
the onion and carrot. Cook until soft, ~{6%minutes}. Add the garlic and cook
for ~{1%minute} more. Add the @lamb mince{200%g} along with the @cinnamon stick{1}
and stir. Cook for ~{5-6%minutes}, until the lamb has browned. Add the @diced
tomatoes{1%400g can}. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and
@ground black pepper{pinch}. Simmer for ~{15-20%minutes} until thick and
tomatoey.

Pop the aubergine on a #baking tray{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{a drizzle},
a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}. Grill for ~{8-9%minutes} on
each side. Remove from your #grill{} and leave to the side (leave your grill
on).

> TIP: The aubergine slices should be browned and soft. If they aren't, grill
> them for a little longer. If they are getting brown too quickly, turn the
> heat down a little.

Halve the @ciabatta{1} (as if you were making a sandwich) and leave to the side.
When the lamb mixture is nice and thick, discard the cinnamon stick and pour
into an #ovenproof dish{}. Lay the aubergine on top and spoon over the
@creme fraiche{112.5%ml}. Spread the crème fraîche with the back of a #spoon{}
and sprinkle over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}. Grill the
moussaka for about ~{5%minutes}, until the top is bubbling and brown.

While the moussaka is browning, put the @wild rocket{40%g} in a #bowl{} with
a drizzle of @olive oil{a drizzle} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and
@black pepper{pinch}. Toss together.

Once brown, remove the moussaka from under your grill. Pop the ciabatta slices
under the grill for ~{2%minutes} on each side, until toasted.

> TIP: Watch they don't burn! Cut the remaining garlic clove in half, take the
> ciabatta out from under your grill and rub the garlic clove across each slice.
> You can also drizzle over a little olive oil.

Cut the remaining garlic clove in half, take the ciabatta out from under your
grill and rub the garlic clove across each slice. You can also drizzle over a
little @?olive oil{a drizzle}. Serve the moussaka with some dressed rocket and
a garlic ciabatta on the side. Enjoy!